spans.text: The daisy painted ground , perfumed the air , And sweet contentment , seemed to banish care , A group of lovely damsels caught my eye , And each in youth and beauty strove to vie ; Yet two shone more resplendent than the rest , One in a purple , airy , flowing vest ; Her temples bound with flowers of different hue , The lily white , the violet azure blue , Her tender feet with glittering sandals bound , Tripped lightly over the flowery painted ground
to banish care , A group of lovely damsels caught my eye
Her tender feet with glittering sandals bound
a heavenly sound , A sound more sweet than the soft breath of love , Harmonious as the songsters of the grove
'Twas virtue's voice , the pure seraphic maid , In tender numbers
— to heaven the music floats , And angels echo back the tuneful notes
woe fraught murmurs reigned throughout the woods
woe fraught murmurs reigned throughout the woods
Fear not , fair nymph , in me alone confide
the virgin , the prophetic sound , And gleams of heavenly light

those which faned the sweet ambrosial gale
Whose power our wishes and our minds
of all the gifts the gods bestow
the stings of conscience can subdue
Welcome , welcome , to our cell , " Here content , and peace
the bosom fire , " All that virtue can desire
